Wouldn't this be an infinite loop? Seems risky to just infinitely try again. I'd recommend doing:
lock.lock();
try {
    return map.put("key" + key, "value" + key);
} finally {
    lock.unlock();
}
This is what the JavaDoc recommends.
Also, if you return the result of map.put, then you don't need the extra return null; at the bottom.

